    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA145-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">iḵtu iravukkuṟi vanta (EN, ER, ET, EV: talaimakaṉ) ciṟaippuṟattāṉākat tōḻi varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante urged for marriage while [HE] who had come for the night tryst was behind the fence.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA145">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            iruṅkaḻi poruta vīra veṇmaṇaṉ</l>
<l>            mākkoṭi yaṭumpiṉ māyita ḻalari</l>
<l>            kūntaṉ makaḷir kōtaik kūṭṭuṅ</l>
<l>            kāmar koṇka ṉāmveṅ kēṇmai</l>
<l>            yamaintē tillā vūṅku nammoṭu </l>
<l>            puṇarntaṉaṉ pōla vuṇarak kūṟit</l>
<l>            tāṉyāṅ keṉṉu maṟaṉi laṉṉai</l>
<l>            yāṉeḻi laṟitalu muriya ṇīyunam</l>
<l>            parāraip puṉṉaic cēri mella</l>
<l>            naḷḷeṉ kaṅkulum varuvarō </l>
<l>            vamma vāḻiyavar tērmaṇik kuralē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent3">Even before there was reason,</l>
<l rend="indent4">since we were attached</l>
<l rend="indent">in warm intimacy to the desirous man from the sea,</l>
<l rend="indent2">where the women join garlands in [their] tresses</l>
<l rend="indent3">from the big-petalled flowers of the Aṭumpu in large creepers,</l>
<l rend="indent4">in the moist white sand beaten by the dark backwaters,</l>
<l>[our] virtueless mother was saying: “where [is] he?”,</l>
<l rend="indent2">talking, as she realises(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">uṇara</term>: or rather adverbially, something like "knowingly"?</note>, as if he had united with us.</l>
<l>It is suitable for her to know too of [my]<note place="foot">How to account for <term xml:lang="ta">yāṉ</term> here? Actually it cannot be read as a genitive to <term xml:lang="ta">eḻil</term>, but still it does not make sense to read it as the subject of <term xml:lang="ta">aṟitalum</term>, because then we would be left without object for <term xml:lang="ta">uriyaḷ</term>.</note> grace. ...(?)<note place="foot">How to integrate <term xml:lang="ta">nīyum</term> into the construction? There is neither a verb of the 2nd sg., nor even an non-finite verb form to connect it with.</note></l>
<l>Will he come, even at deepest night,</l>
<l rend="indent2">softly, to our quarter of large-trunked Puṉṉai trees?</l>
<l>Alas, may the voice of his chariot bells live.</l>
        </lg>
